			<td class="BoardRowA"><a name="6782411"><span style="font-weight: bold;">
				Stupid warriors are better warriors
			</span></a></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Why is it that warriors in EQ follow the 'bigger is better' idea? Large races have all the advantages when it comes to being warriors and NO disadvantages. Don't get started on the 'wah, but the faction..' faction is bullshit, at high level it doesn't matter what your faction is because you can always bind in a place and it's not like you need to run to a inn every 30 minutes to get food and drink.  <br>  <br> So at high level the large, stupid, easy target, clumbsy as hell ogre is one of the better warriors than the smarter, faster, and less lightly to be hit elf... Which is just plain lame. Why should the elf be the 'ogre with fewer hp'? Because that's what they are now. That's just an example of how unbalanced it is.  <br>  <br> I have no problem with the ogre taking more damage and doing more damage due to strength because that's how ogres work. But that damage should be no greater than the elf who is smarter, and thus, could learn how to exploit weaknesses in defense, and use his/her superior speed and agility to strike precise and deadly blows. That's how things work in a real fight. 		

