			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Simply put, Ogres are the best warriors in the game, with trolls a very close second. There are real drawbacks, like having to /petition to get someone AFK to move out of the way so you can zone (like into SolB). Also, you get friends and strangers killed if you are in the way (/rant truthfully it is because a-holes fight at the zone and wont move to let big guys get by, and everyone bitches at you. Used to bother me, but I tell em to deal with it and ignore em /rant off) <br>  <br> Trying to get on a mob in large fights is very hard, we take up so much of the fighting area that you will usually not be on target but 50% of the fight. Shrink potions help, but they are not stackable and wih Verants wonderful servers you tend to go linkdead in those large plane or dragon raids, forcing you to return to normal size. <br>  <br> Size is mostly the issue, but there is a killer shoulder piece that drops in the hole that large races can't wear (think its AC20 +10vs all saves), so I am using a 13ac +10str shoulders; nice, but I'll take 7ac and resistances anyday over 10str. <br>  <br> As for faction, well I can't bind anywhere safely in Kunark (I choose to hunt with my friends in Karnors, if your eveil it ruins Overthere faction). Really though, at my level I've got guildmates and friends who can rez. <br>  <br> Ive got a ton of hit points at the cost of a few ac points (from slighty lower agi). I can hit harder, bash, and I'm dead sexy (ok thats puching it a little). Sure a halfling levels faster blah blah, but thats the choice you make. All warriors are not equal, just like all calsses are not. <br> 		

