		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				technically, from a fencers standpoint, (yes, i am a fencer)the size thing is all off. A larger fighter would have more hp, yet a smaller one, namely the elfs, would be hit MUCH less in combat. <br> the part about the smarter warrior is right: they should be able to do more crits/crips by striking the blade into a weak point, such as bad armor. a larger/stupider race would be far more likely to hit at random, although harder, but not in the weak points that an elf would hit. therefor, the ogre and wood elf warriors should be able to do the same amount of dmg (about). the ogre warrior would be hit more, and have more hps, but the wood elf warrior would be hit less and have less HPs. being a fencer, this game just plain sucks at combat with its hack/slash and random dodge/parry. but i relize that changing that would make the game into an action instead of an RPG, so scratch any of that. the larger race should have the ability to swing over others heads though, as height is a huge advantage because you can reach. yet the smaller races really should be hit less, and therefore makeing them worth playing.		

