		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Exactly. From gnomes to ogres, warriors are very good. Sure it would make sense for agility and dexterity to have more of an effect on gameplay, but they don't. Any race warrior can get ac gear and hitpoint gear. All I'm saying is that the larger races will have a bigger edge in hit points. Also ogres cannot be stunned from the front. Therefore, in my rather 'large' (forgive the pun) experience in playing warriors of all races, ogres make the best. Its very close though to the other races. <br>  <br> Remember though if you don't know what the hell your doing it won't matter that your an ogre, troll or barbarian... I've seen more than my share of bad tanks. <br>  <br> Just play what you want really, like Emile said. It would be a boring game if everyone played the same race/class combo. No one would turn a warrior away based on race, I never seen it.		

